    "Image_Display_Class": "postcard",
    "Image_File_Type": "image",
    "Intro": "<p> I've had a cough for the last couple of weeks. I initially thought\r\n    it was nothing, and just kept training, which felt fine. But it\r\n    held on &amp; got worse rather than better, so I've just stopped\r\n    training altogether &amp; concentrated on getting the rest I\r\n    need.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> I'm finally on the mend &amp; expect to be ready to hit the\r\n    weights again on Friday. But I don't want to just jump back in\r\n    where I left off, so I'll be repeating the second week of\r\n    <em>Mass Made Simple</em> before moving forward &amp; completing\r\n    the program.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> A week off, plus repeating a week means I'll be 2 weeks\r\n    behind. The initial plan was for 7 weeks of mass building, but the\r\n    extra two weeks pushes it to 9, and I'm not sure my body will want\r\n    to do that. So once I hit week #5 of the program (which will be\r\n    week #7 on the calendar) I'll be alert for signs of deeper\r\n    fatigue: lack of motivation, stalled progress, trouble sleeping.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Focusing on next summer has made it <em>much</em> easier to make\r\n    the right decisions this week. I feel like I have plenty of time\r\n    to rest &amp; recover and I'll still be able to bring my A game\r\n    when it matters.\r\n</p>\r\n",
