    "Via_Title": null,
    "Title": "Tahoe Prep: Weeks 16 & 17",
    "Image_File_Name": "20190211-mountain-views.jpg",
    "Image_Display_Class": "postcard",
    "Image_File_Type": "image",
    "Intro": "<p> Last week got super-busy, and also rainy and it was less\r\n    \"structured training\" and more \"doing what I can with whatever's\r\n    rideable around here.\" Lots of loops through neighborhood horse\r\n    trails. Not great for the mental state, but good enough to keep my\r\n    fitness improving.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> This week, it's clear that my chain &amp; chainrings\r\n    are <em>toast</em>. Shark teeth on the rings and the chain is\r\n    stretched all to hell. Replacements are en route. (I got lucky -\r\n    the cassette seems to be in fine shape.)\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> So, how's the training going?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Meh. I rode enough, but didn't climb enough, and <em>gained</em>\r\n    weight. (Work stress, lingering cold, etc., my resolve was weak.)\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> So, what now? Get back after it.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> This week's checklist:\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li> <b>Hard climb 3 days</b>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> <b>Ride 3+ hours</b>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> <b>Drop a pound</b> (Current weight: <b>184.8#</b>)\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n",
