    "Via_Title": null,
    "Title": "More Racing",
    "Image_File_Name": "IMG_7563.JPG",
    "Image_Display_Class": "postcard",
    "Image_File_Type": "image",
    "Intro": "<p> I've realized I'm happier when I race once in a while. I have no\r\n    interest in planning out any kind of structured \"season\", but I do\r\n    want to have something to look for ward to and train for every\r\n    couple of months.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> So far, I'm just collecting options for this fall and next year.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li> I really do want to do a couple of the\r\n        local <a href=\"http://nondotadventures.com/home/races/\">Non\r\n            Dot Adventures</a> races next year. (I feel like I\r\n        have <a href=\"archive/3304\">unfinished business</a> at\r\n        Santiago.)\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> <a href=\"https://rimnordic.com\">Rim Nordic</a>, near Big Bear\r\n        lake, does three races each year. (2019 date TBD?)\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> <a href=\"http://southridgeusa.com/\">Southridge Racing\r\n            Family</a> in Fontana starts their Fall Series on Sept 29-30.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> If I'm aiming to do Leadville at some point, I should\r\n        probably think about doing\r\n        the <a href=\"http://www.tahoetrailmtb.com/\">Tahoe Trail\r\n            MTB</a>.(July 13)\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> I <em>really</em> want to race a few of\r\n        the <a href=\"http://raceoc.com/\">Over the Hump</a> races next\r\n        summer. I didn't make this a priority this year, and I wish I had.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> And there's the annual <a href=\"https://www.active.com/silverado-ca/cycling/mountain-biking/oc-mtb-limestone-xc-race-2018?int=72-3-A1\">Limestone XC</a> race.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li> And the <a href=\"http://www.teambigbear.com/2017-mtb-schedule.html\">Goldstate Race Series</a> has a few dates close to me.\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p> Put all that together, and there are <em>plenty</em> of\r\n    opportunities to race.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> And honestly, I'm really tired of hearing myself say that the best\r\n    thing I can do for my fitness is to lose ten pounds of fat. I know\r\n    better than to take that on right now. But soon, that's going to\r\n    be the focus of my eating &amp; training.\r\n</p>",
