    "Title": "Motivational Self-Talk",
    "Image_File_Name": "have-a-cookie.jpg",
    "Image_Display_Class": "postcard",
    "Image_File_Type": "image",
    "Intro": "<p> I was looking at my <a href=\"archive/3304\">Santiago race\r\n        report</a> from last year, and this jumped out at me:\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n    <p> Browsing through the race day photos, there's a clear\r\n        difference between me and the mid-pack Sport riders. They are\r\n        noticeably leaner than I am. Normally, I wouldn't care. But that's\r\n        reinforced by the race data.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p> I can only imagine what I'd be able to do if I were riding\r\n        more consistently, and not carrying around a gallon of ice cream\r\n        and two batches of cookies everywhere I go.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p> It's time to face the fact that the single best thing I can do\r\n        for my cycling (and probably my health in general) is to drop\r\n        10-15 lbs.\r\n    </p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p> So I'm posting this image in my cube, and I might tape it inside\r\n    the pantry door at home, above the cookies.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> For the record, my bathroom scale says I'm at <b>184.6#, 16% body fat</b>. \r\n</p>",
