    "Title": "Barham Ridge Graded",
    "Image_File_Name": "20170713-barham.jpg",
    "Image_Display_Class": "postcard",
    "Image_File_Type": "image",
    "Intro": "<p> Santiago has been my haven over the last couple of years. To have\r\n    a major part of it erased like this feels like something real has\r\n    been lost. I didn't expect to feel this way, but I do.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> I can grudgingly accept that Barham was originally a fire road,\r\n    and is needed to provide emergency access.  But I've heard rumors\r\n    that the Chutes Trail is next, and that really would be a\r\n    loss. Santiago Oaks is a small park. It doesn't have sweeping\r\n    views or jewel box canyons.  What it <em>does</em> have is local\r\n    access, personality, and technical challenge. Grading these trails\r\n    destroys what's best about this park.\r\n<p> \r\n",
