    "Title": "Coaching Myself",
    "Image_File_Name": "20170710-barbells.jpg",
    "Image_Display_Class": "postcard",
    "Image_File_Type": "image",
    "Intro": "<p> <b>Big Picture</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<dl>\r\n    <dt> Plan on racing next year.\r\n    </dt>\r\n    <dd> Working toward goals makes me happy.\r\n    </dd>\r\n    <dt> Weight training should focus on the basics.\r\n    </dt>\r\n    <dd> Bench press, pull-up, dead lift, squat, loaded carries, and\r\n        Turkish get-ups. Get a squat rack with a pull-up bar.\r\n    </dd>\r\n    <dt> Stretch.\r\n    </dt>\r\n    <dd> Twice a week, <a href=\"archive/2889\">work on mobility</a>.\r\n    </dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n\r\n<p> <b>Details</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<dl>\r\n    <dt> Do some no-hands Turkish get-up variations.\r\n    </dt>\r\n    <dd> My hips have been sore. Some mobility & strength work will do\r\n        them good.\r\n    </dd>\r\n    <dt> Stretch out the lunch loop this week.\r\n    </dt>\r\n    <dd> I've streamlined my lunch ride process. There's time now.\r\n    </dd>\r\n    <dt> Bring lunch from home.\r\n    </dt>\r\n    <dd> The cafe at work is outstanding, but I'm happier eating food\r\n        from home.\r\n    </dd>\r\n</dl>",
